bit like this:</p> <p><img src="data:image/svg+xml,<svg xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot; width=&quot;404&quot; height=&quot;267&quot;><rect fill-opacity=&quot;0&quot;/></svg>" alt="" In most web servers, <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">index.html</code> is a special name that is used as the default file to serve when the user visits a directory. This means that users can type <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">https://YOUR_USERNAME.github.io/YOUR_REPOSITORY_NAME/contact/</code> instead of <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">https://YOUR_USERNAME.github.io/YOUR_REPOSITORY_NAME/contact/index.html</code>.</p> </section><section id="step-7-basic-contact-form-section" class="step" data-step_index="6"><h3 id="step-7-basic-contact-form"><input type="checkbox" data-for="step-7-basic-contact-form" class="step-checkbox"> <a href="#step-7-basic-contact-form" class="anchor-heading" aria-labelledby="step-7-basic-contact-form"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" aria-hidden="true"><use xlink:href="#svg-link"></use></svg></a> Step 7: Basic contact form </h3> <p>In this step we will add a functional contact form to the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">contact</code> page. When the user submits the form, their email client will open with a new email to you, with the subject and body prefilled with the values they entered in the form.</p> <p>Contact forms on the web are not made like this anymore, and for good reasons:</p> <ul> <li>This method exposes your email address to spammers. One of the primary reasons for a contact form is to not expose your email address publicly.</li> <li>The message formatting is awkward and not very user-friendly.</li> </ul> <p>However, making a contact form properly would require server-side code and/or a third-party service, which is way beyond the scope of this first lab.</p> <ol> <li>Create a <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/form" target="_blank"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;form&gt;</code></a> element in <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">contact/index.html</code> and set: <ul> <li>Its <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">action</code> attribute to <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">mailto:YOUR_EMAIL_ADDRESS</code> (e.g. <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">mailto:foo@example.com</code>)</li> <li>Its <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">method</code> attribute to <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Methods/POST"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">POST</code></a></li> <li>Its <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">enctype</code> attribute to <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/form#attr-enctype"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">text/plain</code></a></li> <li>Why do we need the last two? Experiment by using the form without them and see what happens!</li> </ul> </li> <li>Create our contact form fields. We need at least: <ul> <li>A single line text field (<a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input" target="_blank"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;input&gt;</code></a>) for the sender‚Äôs email address with <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">name="email"</code> and <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">type="email"</code></li> <li>A single line text field (<a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input" target="_blank"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;input&gt;</code></a>) for for the subject with <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">name="subject"</code> (you don‚Äôt need <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">type="text"</code> as that is the default)</li> <li>A multiline text field (<a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/textarea" target="_blank"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;textarea&gt;</code></a>) for the actual message with <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">name="body"</code></li> </ul> </li> <li>Wrap each field in a <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/label" target="_blank"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;label&gt;</code></a> with the field name as its contents</li> <li>Add a submit button with <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/button" target="_blank"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;button&gt;</code></a> (you don‚Äôt need <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">type="submit"</code> as that is the default)</li> </ol> <p>The directory structure at this point should look a bit like this:</p> <p><img src="data:image/svg+xml,<svg xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot; width=&quot;404&quot; height=&quot;267&quot;><rect fill-opacity=&quot;0&quot;/></svg>" alt="" style="--natural-width:404;--natural-height:267;background-blend-mode:normal!important;background-clip:content-box!important;background-position:50% 50%!important;background-color:rgba(0,0,0,0)!important;background-image:var(--sf-img-13)!important;background-size:100% 100%!important;background-origin:content-box!important;background-repeat:no-repeat!important"></p> <p class="tip">While developing, you will likely need to try your form multiple times. Add default values to all fields via the HTML (using the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">value</code> attribute on <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input" target="_blank"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;input&gt;</code></a>s and element contents in <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/textarea" target="_blank"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;textarea&gt;</code></a>) so you don‚Äôt have to type them every time.</p> <p>Our contact form should now be functional albeit not very pretty (but don‚Äôt worry about that, that‚Äôs CSS‚Äô job).</p> <figure> <p><a href="https://vis-society.github.io/labs/1/images/screenshots/jie-step7.png" target="_blank"><img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="" style="--natural-width:2598;--natural-height:716"></a></p> <figcaption> An example contact form for Step 7. </figcaption> </figure> <p>Try submitting it and see what happens!</p> <p class="note">Don‚Äôt worry about the appearance of your contact form, we will fix that in Lab 2!
